OL,4,Cpollution in a decade, say campaigners
OL,6,F"Across the globe, the norm is to
OL,7,Fmanage water at a local level, rather
OL,8,Fthan the 100% private ownership model
OL,9,Fin place in England that has proved
OL,10,Fcatastrophic for the environment and
OL,11,Fpublic health.
OL,13,F"The era of broken pipes and broken
OL,14,Fpromises must end and be replaced by a
OL,15,Ffresh vision for water that ends
OL,16,Fpollution for profit and leads to a
OL,17,Ffair and transparent system ` one that
OL,18,Fprioritises public health and value
OL,19,Ffor customer money and delivers
OL,20,Fhealthy coastlines, rivers and lakes."
